  "body": "Geth doesn't work on CentOS/RedHat 6, because GLIBC is too old (2.12 vs. 2.14 require by geth). RedHat 6 is still in use in many potential enterprise adopters of a block chain.\n\nldd --version\nldd (GNU libc) 2.12\nCopyright (C) 2010 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\nThis is free software; see the source for copying conditions.  There is NO\nwarranty; not even for MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.\nWritten by Roland McGrath and Ulrich Drepper.\n\n./geth\n./geth: /lib64/libc.so.6: version `GLIBC_2.14' not found (required by ./geth)\n",
